Description: Handle of Knidian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp; caduceus symbol.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.201, 24. Names, Aristokles and Eniochos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0300)
